By: Staff Reporter JOHANNESBURG, July 13 – Zindzi Mandela, the daughter of South African anti-apartheid icons Nelson Mandela and Winnie Madikizela-Mandela, has died aged 59, local media reported on Monday. Mandela, who was South Africa’s ambassador to Denmark, died in the early hours of Monday after a short illness, public broadcaster SABC reported, citing a family member. 